<section id="about" class="section about">
  <div class="about-inner">
    <div class="about-content">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2 class="section-title">About</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="about-text">
        <p class="about-lead">
          I'm a Software Engineering Researcher and Master's graduate dedicated to exploring
          the rapidly evolving AI landscape — how AI tools and methodologies can elevate
          software quality and system architecture.
        </p>
        <p>
          My roots are in hands-on development: rigorous programming training at <strong>42 Amman</strong>,
          experience as a freelance front-end developer and UI/UX designer, and co-founding
          <strong>Vighting</strong> where I wore both engineering and design hats. I also coordinated
          <strong>MeetPixils</strong>, Jordan's first event for branding and UI/UX designers.
        </p>
        <p>
          That said, I came into this space acutely aware of the trap. AI lets you build faster
          than you learn — features ship, APIs work, and it's tempting to think the job is done.
          But the hard part of software engineering was never writing the code. It's knowing what
          will break, what will scale, what will confuse the next person, what will expose user
          data. AI didn't make those problems go away — it just made them show up faster.
        </p>
        <p>
          So every time I use AI to build, I run the same four checks: Is this secure? Is this
          efficient? What regressions could this introduce? What tests do we need before shipping?
          Understanding was never optional, and the best engineers aren't the ones who write every
          line — they're the ones who know what to verify before they go to prod.
        </p>
        <p>
          Whether I'm analyzing new AI models, drafting research papers, or writing code to test
          a new hypothesis, I'm driven by the desire to build smarter, more intuitive software.
          I believe in continuous learning and building in public.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="about-facts">
      <h3 class="facts-heading">Quick facts</h3>
      <dl class="facts-list">
        <div class="fact">
          <dt class="fact-label">Focus</dt>
          <dd class="fact-value">AI Research, Front-end, UI/UX</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="fact">
          <dt class="fact-label">Education</dt>
          <dd class="fact-value">M.Sc. Software Engineering</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="fact">
          <dt class="fact-label">Training</dt>
          <dd class="fact-value">42 Amman Common Core</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="fact">
          <dt class="fact-label">Location</dt>
          <dd class="fact-value">Amman, Jordan</dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .about-inner {
    max-width: 80rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 var(--space-xl);
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-4xl);
    align-items: start;
  }

  .about-text {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--ink-subtle);
    max-width: 65ch;
  }

  .about-text p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .about-text p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .about-lead {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--ink);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .about-facts {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .facts-heading {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .facts-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .fact {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.25rem;
  }

  .fact-label {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .fact-value {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about-inner {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: var(--space-2xl);
    }
  }
</style>
